            </p>
            <main>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800">How to Build an AI-Powered Upsell Assistant</h1>
                <table>
                    <tr><th>The Problem</th><th>The AI Solution</th></tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Finding upsell opportunities is a manual, high-effort task requiring deep analysis of inventory, historical data, and merchant portfolios.</td>
                        <td>Use NotebookLM as a dedicated "AI Assistant" that you can load with *all* relevant data (inventory, rate cards, merchant history) to find data-driven upsell opportunities.</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <div class="tag-container">
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Primary Roles:</strong> Account Managers, Account Directors</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Tools:</strong> NotebookLM, Google Sheets</span>
                    <span class="tag tag-purple"><strong>Difficulty / Phase:</strong> Phase 3: Advanced AI</span>
                </div>
                <hr class="solution-hr">
                <h2 class="text-2xl mb-4 solution-h2">Step-by-Step Training Workflow</h2>
                <h3 class="text-xl mb-3 solution-h3">Step 1: Create Your "Upsell Notebook"</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">In <strong>NotebookLM</strong>, create a new Notebook named "AM Upsell Assistant - [Your Name]".</p>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 2: Upload Your "Knowledge" Sources</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">This is the most critical step. "Teach" your assistant by uploading these sources:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 pl-4">
                    <li><code>Current Inventory Avails.pdf</code>: All available ad inventory.</li>
                    <li><code>YoY Tenancy Data.csv</code>: What merchants bought this time last year.</li>
                    <li><code>CPAi Data.csv</code>: Performance data for merchants.</li>
                    <li><code>Merchant Portfolio.txt</code>: A simple list of your merchants.</li>
                    <li><code>Rate Cards.pdf</code>: The official rate cards.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3 class="text-xl mt-6 mb-3 solution-h3">Step 3: Ask Strategic Upsell Questions</h3>
                <p class="mb-4">Now, chat with your "assistant" to find opportunities.</p>
                <p><strong>Opportunity Finding:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>Cross-reference the 'YoY Tenancy Data' with the 'Current Inventory'.
Which merchants from my 'Merchant Portfolio' list bought a placement last year but have *not* booked it this year?</code></pre>
                <p class="mt-4"><strong>Strategic Recommendation:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>Based on the 'CPAi Data', which merchant in my portfolio has the highest CVR but is only running on standard placements?
Suggest an upsell package for them from the 'Rate Cards'.</code></pre>
                <p class="mt-4"><strong>Drafting Outreach:</strong></p>
                <pre><code>Draft a short, 3-paragraph outreach email to [Merchant Name]. 
Reference their strong performance last year (from 'YoY Tenancy') and offer them the [Package Name] from the 'Rate Card'.</code></pre>
